<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-589-382  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 589 382.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  June 25 1990 n306 p12(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MCI's package deal: service aimed at smaller businesses. (MCICommunications Corp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Sweeney, Terry.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>MCI Communications Corp announces Vision, a long-distance servicethat offers package rates, volume discounts for peak usage andfeatures that can be tailored to the needs of individualbusinesses.andP;  Additionally, Vision, which targets small and mediumbusinesses, offers consolidated billing and an individual customerservice representative.andP;  The flat rate for the service is 20 centsper minute with six-second billing increments.andP;  Vision's automatic'ringdown' feature is similar to call forwarding.andP;  The servicealso features remote exchange capability and users can rely onVision to reduce their local market testing expenses.andP;  Vision willbe available in July 1990.andP;  MCI has a 15 percent share of the $18billion general business telephone user segment.andP;  That share willincrease if MCI's bid to acquire Telecom*USA is approved.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (services).andO;Ticker:    MCIC.andO;Topic:     TelecommunicationsPriceCost of CommunicationsTelephone CompaniesTelephone Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>